oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The Commoner
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The Commoner (horse) being held by a stable hand.

The Commoner (1892-1914) had 18 wins during his career as a racehorse, including McGrathiana Stud Stakes, Essex Stakes, and the Cincinnati Press Stakes. In 1901, General William H. Jackson purchased him for $15,000 to be a stud at Belle Meade.
